## AI work log — mandatory workflow

This project keeps a **tracked** changelog at the repo root: **`AI_WORK_LOG.md`**.

### Before you write or change code

1. **Read `AI_WORK_LOG.md`** — follow **§0 Mandatory pre-task review** in **`.cursor/rules/ai-work-log-protocol.mdc`**: full **Current conventions**, **last five** log entries (newest first), and **extra entries** when the task overlaps logged areas. Check overlap, compatibility, and regression risk against **“Do not undo”** bullets **before** planning or coding.
2. Align new work with those conventions. If the user asks for something that conflicts, **call out the conflict** and propose an explicit trade-off instead of silently undoing prior decisions.

### After you complete a task (or a coherent batch of changes)

1. **Append a new entry** at the top of the **Log** section in `AI_WORK_LOG.md` (keep **newest first**).
2. Each entry should include: **ISO date**, **short title**, **what changed** (paths or feature areas), **why** (intent), and **“Do not undo”** bullets when future work could easily regress the fix.
3. If you introduced or changed a **long-lived convention** (routing, i18n, perf, a11y patterns, legal/licence), update the **Current conventions** section in the same file.
4. **Never** put secrets, API keys, or `.env` contents in the log.

### Relation to other docs

- **`REPAIR_LOG.md`** — security / audit-oriented history; do not duplicate it verbatim in `AI_WORK_LOG.md`; cross-reference when useful.
- **`README.md`** — user-facing architecture; update when behaviour or structure changes materially.
